The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Toshiba eyes $1bn revenue
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Toshiba eyes $1bn revenue
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                          Toshiba India MD Yuzo Kato in Mumbai on Tuesday. (Fotocorp)                                  
	Mumbai, April 15: Toshiba, the Japanese technology firm, today unveiled a range of notebooks and home appliances in the country and signalled its desire to ramp up revenues from India to $1 billion by 2015.        
	The electrical and electronic equipment manufacturer hopes to enhance its market share in the consumer products segment to 10 per cent by 2010 from less than 5 per cent now.         
	Toshibas Satellite notebooks come with built-in FM tuner, DVD Super multi-drive DVD writer, webcam with face recognition, advanced bluetooth technology and fingerprint recognition system.         
	The models will retail in the price range of Rs 27,990 to Rs 72,990. According to the International Data Corporation, about 16 lakh laptops were sold in India in 2007.         
	The company is looking at a market share of about 15 per cent in the notebook market by 2010.         
	We are trying to achieve growth greater than current GDP growth in the country, said Yuzo Kato, managing director of Toshiba India.        
	The company has also announced the Regza series of LCD television.         
	The TVs will be available with screen sizes varying from 32 inches to 57 inches, with prices ranging from Rs 51,000 to Rs 4,80,000.         
	In refrigerators, Toshiba will offer 20 models with capacities varying between 321 and 614 litres, at prices between Rs 23,490 and Rs 64,990. The company has also launched four models of washing machines, with the basic model priced at Rs 16,500.         
	The Indian refrigerator market is estimated at 45 lakh units, the washing machine market at 22.5 lakh units, and the LCD TV market at 7 lakh units a year.                                                                                                                                     
